    Pence sits near Kim Jong Un’s sister, doesn't applaud unified Korean Olympians
    At the Opening Ceremonies of the Olympics on Feb. 9, Vice President Pence was seated near Kim Yo Jong, North Korean leader Kim Jong Un’s younger sister, and did not applaud when North and South Koreans marched together.
